CVE-2022-3509,PL-22699,138317,Sub-task,Done,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,Done,Aurélien Loyer,5cf635cac756c10f35f292f4,Aurélien Loyer,5cf635cac756c10f35f292f4,Aurélien Loyer,5cf635cac756c10f35f292f4,26/Jul/24 3:40 PM,26/Jul/24 4:12 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,26/Jul/24 4:12 PM,,,,,0,security,support,,,,"[https://curl.se/docs/CVE-2024-2398.html

When an application tells libcurl it wants to allow HTTP/2 server push, and the amount of received headers for the push surpasses the maximum allowed limit (1000), libcurl aborts the server push. When aborting, libcurl inadvertently does not free all the previously allocated headers and instead leaks the memory.
Further, this error condition fails silently and is therefore not easily detected by an application.
If a server sends many {{PUSH_PROMISE}} frames with an excessive amount of headers, this can lead to multiple megabytes of memory leaked _per response_.
HTTP/2 server push is a relatively rarely used feature.
The Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) project has assigned the name CVE-2024-2398 to this issue.
CWE-772: Missing Release of Resource after Effective Lifetime

The amount of monthly operation reward spreadsheet should be consistent with the record in the system.",,Automation for Jira,Chengfu Xie,Mack Ding,maysuen,,,,,,,,,,,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,557058:4c9ddcc0-9215-4783-9a9a-6bed06b66d57,626602b9bae0c1006faae8a5,622259ab49c90000702089ce,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,26/Jul/24 2:33 PM;cxie;Screenshot 2024-07-26 124821.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/237053,26/Jul/24 2:45 PM;cxie;Screenshot 2024-07-26 144418.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/237057,26/Jul/24 10:53 AM;ug:31a89b9d-9ca0-4b08-8ff9-3f8064aa5377;image-20240726-024854.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236988,26/Jul/24 10:53 AM;ug:31a89b9d-9ca0-4b08-8ff9-3f8064aa5377;image-20240726-024944.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236989,26/Jul/24 10:53 AM;ug:31a89b9d-9ca0-4b08-8ff9-3f8064aa5377;image-20240726-025140.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236987,26/Jul/24 3:44 PM;ug:5f3fdb02-4e28-402b-a176-aa04f49df18e;image-20240726-074419.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/237082,26/Jul/24 3:44 PM;ug:5f3fdb02-4e28-402b-a176-aa04f49df18e;image-20240726-074431.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/237081,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,claim-cloud,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@126d7711,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,cxie,,,"{repository={count=5, dataType=repository}, json={""cachedValue"":{""errors"":[],""summary"":{""repository"":{""overall"":{""count"":5,""lastUpdated"":""2024-07-26T17:24:31.000+0800"",""dataType"":""repository""},""byInstanceType"":{""GitHub"":{""count"":5,""name"":""GitHub""}}}}},""isStale"":true}}",,,,,,,,,,PROD,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

column1: [BO] Add Shippers from Non-Accredited Audits,SP-18286,138289,Improvement,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,Medium,,,,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,26/Jul/24 4:58 AM,26/Jul/24 7:20 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. Context

For Non-Accredited Audits, such as those for Costco, it is mandatory for the client to have Shippers. Currently, Shippers can be created from myQIMA and added to the Booking form for Costco. It is also possible to add Costco after the booking from QSP in the Non-Accredited Audits view. However, it is not possible to add Shippers through this method.
+*We must allow users to add Shippers in QSP if they were previously created in myQIMA.*+
* Always display all Shippers from the Producer’s order
* Allow checking the Shippers in the grip
Given I’m logged in with any role, expect a Technical Reviewer
And access an onder with any status, except Finished
When I navigate to the Non-Accredited Audits view
+Then I must see all Shippers from the producer that were previously created in myQIMA+
Then I must be able to edit the information on the screen
+And check each one of the Shippers+
+And check all of them by clicking on the header+
+Then the system must save the log in the History view+

Remove stale ignored trivy issues 🧹,PL-22662,138231,Deployment subtask,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,,Aurélien Loyer,5cf635cac756c10f35f292f4,Automation for Jira,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,Automation for Jira,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,25/Jul/24 3:44 PM,25/Jul/24 3:44 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,support,,,,,"- Clone the latest version of the repository.
- Remove all CVEs from the .trivyignore file.

- Run the Trivy check locally by following the steps described in https://qima.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/IT/pages/1279394044/Runbook+-+Docker+image+vulnerabilities+scanning#Testing-the-new-image-locally . You can use the latest develop images to run the script https://github.com/asiainspection/k8s-apps-descriptors/blob/integration/kustomize/environments/apps-integration/kustomization.yml

- If the list of detected vulnerabilities differs from in any way, modify the .trivyignore file, commit the changes and create a Pull Request, eg. https://github.com/asiainspection/qima-platform/pull/7425

Monitor 🔎 production logs to spot issues,PL-22661,138230,Deployment subtask,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,,Aurélien Loyer,5cf635cac756c10f35f292f4,Automation for Jira,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,Automation for Jira,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,25/Jul/24 3:44 PM,25/Jul/24 3:44 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,support,,,,,"Support team should constantly monitor/check logs to identify issues.
Based on the findings, create a task that’s linked to this ticket to fix the issue either on the current release or in the upcoming one.

At the beginning of the support sprint choose a person responsible for logs monitoring and assign them to this ticket. It is crucial to check logs on Thursday to see if the new prod release did not bring any new issues.
Apply these filters manually while investigating traces to extract useful information about slow requests: 👉 MinLatency:2000 /http/host:app.qimaone http.path:/api 👈

Validation for Certification Options and Number of Fields,SP-18199,138139,Epic,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,N/A,,,,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,24/Jul/24 10:26 PM,24/Jul/24 10:31 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h1. Context
* +*Applies if: The applicant is a single producer without multiple production sites.*+
* *Certificate Holder:* The individual producer becomes the certificate holder upon certification.
* *Regulations:* The certification must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations for individual producers.
* +*Applies if:*+ +*The applicant is an entity with multiple production sites*+ and Each production site operates independently without a central QMS.
* *Certificate Holder:* Each individual production site under the entity can become the certificate holder upon certification.
* *Regulations:* Each site must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations individually. and sach site is independently audited and must maintain its own compliance records.
* +*Applies if*++:+ +*The applicant is an entity with multiple production sites*++,+ and there is a centralized QMS that oversees all production and compliance activities.
* *Certificate Holder*: The central management entity or main organization managing all sites under the QMS becomes the certificate holder upon certification.
* *Regulations:* Must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations for multisite operations with a centralized QMS, and requires comprehensive documentation of the QMS and internal procedures.
* *Applies if:* +*Multiple individual producers group together to form a single management entity*+. and the management entity oversees all group members and ensures their compliance.
* *Certificate Holder:* The central management entity of the producer group becomes the certificate holder upon certification.

* *Regulations:* Must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations for group certification, requires documentation of group management procedures, internal audits, and corrective action plans, and regular internal inspections of the individual group members are necessary to maintain compliance.
+*Currently, QIMAcert has no validation between “Certification Options” and the number of fields*+
* Create validation during booking on myQIMA

[IRP] To add IRP: Coordination Team role for the Factory Management,SP-18196,138133,Story,Done,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,Waiting to Release,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,24/Jul/24 4:54 PM,26/Jul/24 4:10 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,26/Jul/24 4:10 PM,SP-202407-W31,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. Current Behavior

* Currently the “factory management” button at order level in IRP is only accessible for manager role “IRP: Coordination manager“, while in daily operations it’s usually the specialist / supervisor that needs to create data, who instead just edit the plain text at order level, which causes more data issues and repetitive work.
* To add the new role “IRP: Coordination team” for this button
** So that coordination specialist, supervisor, leader and manager can all access and manage factory master data.

[BO] Validation for Certification Options and Number of Fields,SP-18183,138116,Improvement,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,N/A,,,,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,24/Jul/24 6:15 AM,24/Jul/24 11:00 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. Context
* +*Applies if: The applicant is a single producer without multiple production sites.*+
* *Certificate Holder:* The individual producer becomes the certificate holder upon certification.
* *Regulations:* The certification must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations for individual producers.
* +*Applies if:*+ +*The applicant is an entity with multiple production sites*+ and Each production site operates independently without a central QMS.
* *Certificate Holder:* Each individual production site under the entity can become the certificate holder upon certification.
* *Regulations:* Each site must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations individually. and sach site is independently audited and must maintain its own compliance records.
* +*Applies if*++:+ +*The applicant is an entity with multiple production sites*++,+ and there is a centralized QMS that oversees all production and compliance activities.
* *Certificate Holder*: The central management entity or main organization managing all sites under the QMS becomes the certificate holder upon certification.
* *Regulations:* Must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations for multisite operations with a centralized QMS, and requires comprehensive documentation of the QMS and internal procedures.
* *Applies if:* +*Multiple individual producers group together to form a single management entity*+. and the management entity oversees all group members and ensures their compliance.
* *Certificate Holder:* The central management entity of the producer group becomes the certificate holder upon certification.

* *Regulations:* Must adhere to GLOBALG.A.P.'s general regulations for group certification, requires documentation of group management procedures, internal audits, and corrective action plans, and regular internal inspections of the individual group members are necessary to maintain compliance.
+*Currently, QSP has not validation between Certification Option and the number of Fields*+
* Create a validation between Certification Option and the number of Fields
** *Option 1: Multisite without QMS”, Option 1: Multisite with QMS* or *Option 2* *Group of Producers”* and *more than one field*
*** Display an warning message in the header “Only one field allowed for Individual Producer certification”
** *Option 1: Multisite without QMS”, Option 1: Multisite with QMS* or *Option 2* *Group of Producers”* and *only one field*
*** Display an warning message in the header “Only more than one field allowed for {one of the respective message above}”
* Block all actions in the system wochi would allow the user procedd with the order
** Exepcted by Add and Remove fields
h3. Scenario 1: Changing Certification Option to ""Option 1 - Individual Producer"" with Multiple Fields
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the order has more than one field
*When* I change the Certification Option to ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*Then* a warning message must be displayed in the header in orange: ""Only one field allowed for Individual Producer certification.""
*And* all actions except adding or removing fields and updating the certification option must be blocked.
h3. Scenario 2: Changing Certification Option to Require More Than One Field with Only One Field
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the order has only one field
*When* I change the Certification Option to ""Option 1: Multisite without QMS"", ""Option 1: Multisite with QMS"", or ""Option 2: Group of Producers""
*Then* a warning message must be displayed in the header in orange: ""More than one field required for [respective Certification Option].""
*And* all actions except adding or removing fields and updating the certification option must be blocked.
h3. Scenario 3: Removing Extra Fields After Warning for Individual Producer
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the order has more than one field
*And* the Certification Option is set to ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*And* I see the warning message: ""Only one field allowed for Individual Producer certification.""
*When* I remove the extra fields, leaving only one
*And* blocked actions should now be enabled.
h3. Scenario 4: Adding Additional Fields After Warning for Options Requiring More Than One Field
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the order has only one field
*And* the Certification Option is set to ""Option 1: Multisite without QMS"", ""Option 1: Multisite with QMS"", or ""Option 2: Group of Producers""
*And* I see the warning message: ""More than one field required for [respective Certification Option].""
*When* I add additional fields, making the total more than one
*And* blocked actions should now be enabled.
h3. Scenario 5: Changing Certification Option After Warning for Individual Producer
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the order has more than one field
*And* the Certification Option is set to ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*And* I see the warning message: ""Only one field allowed for Individual Producer certification.""
*When* I change the Certification Option to any option except ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*And* blocked actions should now be enabled.
h3. Scenario 6: Changing Certification Option After Warning for Options Requiring More Than One Field
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the order has only one field
*And* the Certification Option is set to ""Option 1: Multisite without QMS"", ""Option 1: Multisite with QMS"", or ""Option 2: Group of Producers""
*And* I see the warning message: ""More than one field required for [respective Certification Option].""
*When* I change the Certification Option to ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*And* blocked actions should now be enabled.
h3. Scenario 7: Adding More Fields to Order with ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*Given* I’m logged in to the QSP with any role, except Technical Manager
*And* I access an order in any status, except ""Finished""
*And* the Certification Option is set to ""Option 1 - Individual Producer""
*When* I add more fields, resulting in more than one field
*Then* a warning message must be displayed in the header in orange: ""Only one field allowed for Individual Producer certification.""
*And* all actions except adding or removing fields and updating the certification option must be blocked.
Block the user to move foward with the orders for those cases ✅

+*Currently, myQIMA does not validate the information provided in Section 1: “Select the Certification Options” with the number of fields selected in Section 2 of the booking form.*+
* Create a validation for when the certification option selected is *""Option 1 - Individual Producer""* in Section 1 when the user tries to move foward with more than one field

* Create a validation for when the certification option selected is *“Option 1: Multisite without QMS”, Option 1: Multisite with QMS* or  *Option 2* *Group of Producers”* in Section 1 when the user tries to move foward with only on field
* Display an error message if more than one field is selected.
myQIMA → Book now → Globa.G.A.P certificate → Section 2
*Given* I’m logged in to myQIMA and booking a Global.G.A.P certificate:
*When* I select the certification option “Option 1 - Individual” in Section 1.
*And* I fill out the remaining mandatory information.
*And* I add more than one field
*When* I try to proceed to Section 3
*Then* the system must display an error message: “Only one field can be selected for Option 1: Individual.”
*And* I must not be able to proceed to Section 3.
*When* I remove the extra fields, leaving only one
*Then* I must be able to proceed to Section 3.
*Given* I’m logged in to myQIMA and booking a Global.G.A.P certificate:
*When* I select the certification option “Option 1: Multisite without QMS”, Option 1: Multisite with QMS or  Option 2 Group of Producers”
*And* I fill out the remaining mandatory information.
*When* I try to proceed to Section 3
*Then* the system must display an error message: “Only more than one field allowed for {one of the respective message above}.”
*And* I must not be able to proceed to Section 3.
*Then* I must be able to proceed to Section 3.

[myQ] Display only Producer's linked Facilities in GlobalG.A.P booking form,SP-18181,138113,Bug,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,Medium,,,,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,24/Jul/24 12:40 AM,24/Jul/24 8:55 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. Context

Fields and facilities must always be linked to a producer. This is the first step in the form when creating these units. When booking a food certification order, a producer is selected in Section 1, followed by selecting the fields and facilities in Section 2. Currently, the system only displays fields associated with the selected producer, but it shows all facilities instead of only those linked to the producer.
Adjust the behavior in the GlobalG.A.P. Booking form to display only the facilities previously created for the selected producer.
myQIMA → Book now → Global.G.A.P Certification → Section 2
*And* I fill out all mandatory information in Section 1
*And* I select a producer in Section 1
*And* I must see only the facilities associated with the selected producer

column1: Analysis,PL-22623,138084,Sub-task,Done,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,Done,Lucas Renard,61cd9be1e763790068b95db5,Lucas Renard,61cd9be1e763790068b95db5,Lucas Renard,61cd9be1e763790068b95db5,23/Jul/24 5:23 PM,25/Jul/24 9:11 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,25/Jul/24 9:11 PM,,,,,0,,,,,,"h1. Context
API pods are OOM killed at 75% of 5GB = 3.75GB
We see a lot of {{Unable to close S3 connection \u003d\u003e S3Object is null}} but none {{Failed to close S3Object}} so we seem to handle finally the closing of the S3 connection in the catch below
log.info(""Unable to close S3 connection => S3Object is null"");
log.error(""Failed to close S3Object {}"", object, ioEx);

We also see {{DataSource health check failed\norg.springframework.jdbc.CannotGetJdbcConnectionException: Failed to obtain JDBC Connection; nested exception is java.sql.SQLTransientConnectionException: Hikari - Connection is not available, request timed out after 30000ms}}
at the end of the logs
{color:#ff991f}(might be linked to the dying pod){color}
h1. *Analyse the heap dump files using a too (here Intellij)*
*First file api-7f85ff56b7-drx8g-202407190841.hprof seems to be corrupted:*
*Second file analysis following documentation* [*Analyze the memory snapshot
{color:#ff991f}2.54 GB for byte[] is huge => issue with file streams ? Link with error {color}{{Unable to close S3 connection \u003d\u003e S3Object is null}}{color:#ff991f} ?{color}
{color:#ff991f}Why is the {color}{{StatefulPersistenceContext}}{color:#ff991f} taking so much memory ? Is it link to dirty sessions we should fix ?{color}
{color:#ff991f}When looking at the entitiesByKey/table nodes, there are mostly Workflow entities that are kept in the dirty context{color}
See: [The anatomy of Hibernate dirty checking mechanism - Vlad Mihalcea
Summary (general information, for example, the total size, number of instances and stack traces of the threads)
[Prometheus Time Series Collection and Processing Server (qima.dev)
=> We are not reaching the 50 max connexion limitation
Looking at other heap files like api-696d5d4f9b-xg2tn-202407241448.hprof, we see the same symptoms:
* A huge Hibernate StateFulPersistenceContext containing Workflow entities
* {color:#ff991f}2.54 GB for byte[] is huge => issue with file streams ? Link with errors {color}{{Unable to close S3 connection \u003d\u003e S3Object is null}}{color:#ff991f} ?{color}
** {color:#ff991f}Check if we can test it by reproducing the S3 error on sandbox{color}
* {color:#ff991f}Hibernate dirty checking issues or overuse in QIMAone ? (see the big usage >1GB of a {color}{{StatefulPersistenceContext}}{color:#ff991f} in PROD){color}

** {color:#ff991f}Consider readonly transactions to avoid dirty checking: {color}[{color:#ff991f}chore: add readonly transaction to reduce dirty checking memory usage by lrenard-qima · Pull Request #9004 · asiainspection/qima-platform (github.com){color}
* {color:#ff991f}We have a lot of retained memory linked to Workflow entities{color}
** {color:#ff991f}Check Intellij warning on calling nested transactional methods of the same service{color}
* {color:#ff991f}We are rarely fetching needed collections withing HQL queries which leads to unecessary overload by doing n queries instead of 1 (see JOIN FETCH HQL keyword){color}
** {color:#ff991f}For this it would be nice to configure a plugin to log the number of queries done for each transaction to see to which level we are not optimizing querying of the database{color}
* {{DataSource health check failed\norg.springframework.jdbc.CannotGetJdbcConnectionException: Failed to obtain JDBC Connection}}{color:#ff991f} before the POD was killed{color}
* [{color:#ff991f}10 Common Hibernate Mistakes That Cripple Your Performance (thorben-janssen.com){color}

Requirements & Problems

* When the user changes the defect AQL to a fixed quantity, we ask the user to fill in different AQL, but for some users who are used to AQL system, they are trying to input 2.5, 4.5 etc. But actually, we are asking them to fill a fixed accept point
* Also regarding flexible level & percentage for measurements, we cannot call it, we should call it Accept point, so the user fill in a percentage as accept point
* Also to find a better way to display, view, edit AQL for defects and for measurements
* Standard level & AQL (I think we can change this one to Recommended level & AQL as wording)  > ISO 2859-1
h2. Potential impacted places in QIMAone
* Inspection type settings: Edit and view
* Booking flow: inspection step + summary step
* Inspector: inspection details page, product page
* Inspector to-do list: quantity step, defect step, measurement step, summary review

[UI] Handling of the edge cases to ensure data consistency and layout,SP-18172,138044,Story,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,,,,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,22/Jul/24 3:43 PM,26/Jul/24 5:33 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. Task
* For the AQL part (result,  CRI/MAJ/MIN found & allowed numbers),
* Consider, test and handle edge cases
** Too much info that exceeding 1 page (investigate & test)
**** if exceed, then to remove one of the worth noting bullet points
***** if there’s only one worth noting, then to remove the last point of non-comfornities
We have made some estimations on the number of characters and bullet points we could cover: *up to 10 bullet points and 700 characters.*
** Test fields with maximum allowed character lengths (e.g., name, title, summary).
** Ensure proper display without overflow or truncation.
** Test fields with minimum allowed character lengths, including empty fields if permissible.
** Ensure there are no errors or layout issues.
** Include special characters (e.g., &, %, *, <, >) in text fields.
** Verify correct encoding and display without causing issues in HTML rendering.
** Add exceptionally long words without spaces in text fields.
** Ensure proper wrapping or truncation to maintain layout integrity.
** Include images of varying sizes, especially oversized ones.
** Ensure images are resized or contained within designated areas without breaking the layout.
** Test the page's print version, ensuring it renders correctly and all information is clear and readable.
** Incorporate an unusually long summary and verify if it overflows to the next page or if mechanisms are in place (e.g., truncation, pagination).

QIMA IT Support Ticket #390410: Modify the reference sample status,SP-18170,138040,Story,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,,,,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,Eric Wang,606c02be4532c90069639932,22/Jul/24 3:16 PM,22/Jul/24 3:29 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. User Story
I want to be notified when client edits the sample key information,
So that I will act accordingly.
* For PSI service reference sample, when client EDITs the below fields

Subject: *[Reference sample update Reminder]*  ${serviceName} of  ${productName} on ${inspDate} #if(${clientReference} != """")  (your ref: ${clientReference} #elseif(${orderNumber} != """")  (QIMA ref: ${orderNumber} #else  (N/A #end )
The reference sample information has just updated that:
Please track the sample information to ensure it reaches the factory correctly!
Existing sample notification for new orders sent to Sample Team:

Given that I am a sample team member, when the client edits one of the above mentioned fields in ACA after new booking that I can receive a notification email with above subject and content. column1: fee update to Zero : R-Cloud-24082666,DAT-1812,138039,Task,Done,DAT,Data,software,juliette.savey,61236080fc55090071e2e029,,,N/A,Done,Jojo Nava,712020:944bc4cb-8baf-4752-ba9e-9b12a04923a5,Sandeep Kumar,557058:68b429f5-380c-4099-aba1-53f58bec72cd,Sandeep Kumar,557058:68b429f5-380c-4099-aba1-53f58bec72cd,22/Jul/24 3:15 PM,23/Jul/24 12:25 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,23/Jul/24 12:25 PM,,,,,0,,,,,,"CURRENT BEHAVIOR:

I want to auto calculate the sample size per reference with double sampling,

*** e.g. with *R-Cloud-24166479*, the sample size should be 80 pcs, instead of 125 pcs (now).
For PO q'ty 1500 PCS and 2500 PCS, by referring to the table below, the sample size should be 80 pcs.

Given that I am a protocol team member, that I can see the sample size per reference level with double sampling method has auto calculated sample size according to the chart. User story
I want to make some adjustments
So that can reduce the rate of sync error
For the incomplete accounts, can sent to NS and will have over thousand errors on the NS
So we want to make some improvement
Before we improve something, we need to investigate first, to export the data for better investigation:
* In QIMA Customer: the account information with the ""State"" empty (under US, Brazil, and India)
** Export: Company name, Link, SIC, Country, State field
* In QIMA Customer: the account list with the phone number of less than 7 digital
** Export: Company name, Link, SIC, Main Contact-Phone number, Accounting contact-Tel

column1: Does this mean that someone could create ‘email@domain.com’ and 'email@domain.com ' logins? What potential issues could arise in this case?

,23/Jul/24 10:15 AM;5feaaa1bd3649601397710f1;Hi [~accountid:61a7a530f24150007216df71] , I just tried in PP env to append a blank to my test account and it turns out the login function is not impacted at least. As this search is a very under-layer method and is used by many places, very hard to tell what is impacting, however, after the change is released this time, the potential risk should be clear.

Also I’m considering how these data come into QSP customer-service, I checked the QIMA website login page and found the validation is there, and also, there is no entrance to edit it in the customer-service, so I suspect these data might be imported from other systems via API calls. maybe in the future, we need to pay more attention to this.",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Done,22/Jul/24 5:31 PM

column3: Add a field to add the last invoice sent,NC-443,137997,Task,Done,NC,No-Code,software,Charles Poquet,61543feed9820f00705d415e,,,Medium,Done,Alexandre Dumont,712020:aca05b73-472d-4f09-ad34-038f612a8bb6,Karla MONDRAGON,608fe66ea56f2f006f0b7961,Karla MONDRAGON,608fe66ea56f2f006f0b7961,19/Jul/24 9:23 PM,26/Jul/24 7:38 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,26/Jul/24 7:38 PM,,,,,0,,,,,,"*As a:* Customer Success Manager (CSM) without access to Netsuite

column1: *I want to:* Access the most recent invoice sent to customers directly through Bubble Billing
*So that:* I can have the last invoice sent to my customer.
*Addition of a Field:* There should be an additional field in Bubble Billing where support staff can upload the last invoice or the SO sent to the customer.
* The Customer Success team comprises customer success support and customer success managers/leaders.
*** Following up with customers to ensure QIMA receives payments for using the platform.
*** Acting as trusted advisors to customers.
*** They do *not* engage in financial issues or sending invoices.
* Not all CSMs have access to Netsuite, the invoicing tool, due to budget constraints.

column1: You are a helpful quality control inspector support bot who answers questions from inspectors in the field. Keep your answers concise (no more than 3 sentences) and simple for someone who is a non-native English speaker. Try your best to answer the questions, the inspectors need your help!
Base your answers on the information in your knowledge base to answer questions.
If you are unsure of which client this request relates to, ask the user to clarify which client they are talking about.

If the user's question is more of an FYI comment, you can acknowledge it and thank the user for the update.",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,137231,Enhancements,In Progress,19/Jul/24 4:11 PM

column1: How to calculate measurement sample size and result of a combined inspection,PL-22585,137950,Improvement,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,High,,,,Nan Chen,5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f,Nan Chen,5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f,18/Jul/24 11:56 PM,25/Jul/24 5:42 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
we need to agree on the business rules and product decision before ""fixing"" something
User case: combined inspection with measurement checklist
First statement: we always calculate Measurement simple size with ordered quantity.

column2: {color:#ff5630}*Issue or not:*{color} the system gives 32 sample size for each product

column1: {color:#36b37e}*Need to be or not:*{color}{color:#36b37e} {color}as it’s one measurement AQL per inspection, we should dispatch sample size 32 to 2 products.
{color:#ff991f}Rules to define: dispatch equally or depending on quantity ratio? {color}
column2: Entered 3 wrong POM for first product

column1: Entered 1 wrong POM for second product
I assume that the total POM out of tolerance is bigger than 3

column2: {color:#ff5630}*Issue or not:*{color} the system gives 32 sample size for each product

column1: First product has 587 POMs in total for 32 samples, so 5% = 28 (round down)
Second product has 192 POMs in total for 32 samples, so 5% = 9 (round down)
{color:#36b37e}*Need to be or not:*{color}{color:#36b37e} {color}as it’s one measurement AQL per inspection, we should dispatch sample size 32 to 2 products.
{color:#ff991f}Rules to define: dispatch equally or depending on quantity ratio? {color}
Then the result should be based on 5% of total POM of sampled product 1 and product 2
column2: Entered 25 wrong POMs for first product

column1: Entered 6 wrong POMs for second product
Summary review shows fail, I assume that 31 is bigger than 28 for first product
{color:#ff991f}Need to define what and how we want to dispatch samples, how to calculate the result{color}

Looks like Result = {color:#bf2600}*Point of Measure Fail*{color} > Accept Point ==> Fail.  So the calculation of result is base on Checkpoints not Item/Sample.

column3: smart-link] ","23/Jul/24 11:20 PM;5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f;[~accountid:5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8]  I created ticket 18011 in the past.

column1: And I closed it as WON’T do. Because some customers need the measurement result based on Point of measurement (POM) out of tolerance

That’s why for the new Simplified measurements checklist, we let the user choose result based on Sample out of tolerance or POM out of tolerance","24/Jul/24 12:28 AM;5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8;[~accountid:5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f] , I think the problem is we don’t have MEASUREMENT SAMPLE SIZE PER PRODUCT.  Each product have different Quantity and should therefore have different sample size.  Right now, we put the TOTAL sample size in all the products (wrong), even if the actual quantity of some product is lower than the sample size.

Because we do not have Measurement sample size per product, we are only using the {color:#bf2600}*TOTAL* {color}sample size, therefore the result calculation is also base on {color:#bf2600}*TOTAL*{color} Checkpoints.  NOT per product.  If we want to calculate the result per product, then we should also have sampling size per product where the calculation will be taken from.
It is the same with Defects-Per-Product, there is only 1 Sample size, so the result is calculated base on Total number of defects of all products, not per product.
This is an example of a product with quantity of 10, but a sample size of 125.
I didn’t understand why we calculated the TOTAL sample size based on the TOTAL quantity in booking (correct IMO), but we displayed this TOTAL sample size for each product in the inspector app. 😞
I said, OK, it’s already done like this, so be it.
But you found the case that it didn’t make sense at all: Sample size can be bigger than the product quantity.
I updated accordingly in the ticket description. ",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,To Do,18/Jul/24 11:56 PM

Improve the detection of @qima.com email addresses in the front end of QIMAconnect.,QID-242,137929,Task,To Do,QID,QIMA connect,software,Gabriel Pascual,5c3c6b139f443a65fecc24e1,,,N/A,,Gabriel Pascual,5c3c6b139f443a65fecc24e1,Vincent Roche,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,Vincent Roche,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,18/Jul/24 6:15 PM,19/Jul/24 3:35 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,qimaone,support,,,,To enhance the user experience and ensure the correct authentication flow for @qima.com email addresses in QIMAconnect. Currently, the authentication process checks with Microsoft O365 to determine the existence of the email, hiding the password field if it exists. However, in some regions, this check is slow, and users can inadvertently enter a password. We need to show a message or block the user from entering a password until the verification is complete.
#* Implement functionality to immediately show a message or block user inputs when an email with the @qima.com domain is entered in the login field.
#* Display a message informing the user to wait for verification when an @qima.com email is detected.
#* Block the password field temporarily until the verification check with Microsoft O365 is complete.
#* Optimize the verification check to ensure it completes in a reasonable timeframe in all regions.
#* Ensure that the message or blocking mechanism works seamlessly across all regions, accounting for potential latency.
#* Test the new detection mechanism thoroughly in different regions to ensure consistent performance.
#* Validate that users with @qima.com email addresses cannot enter a password until the verification is done and that authentication proceeds smoothly via Microsoft O365 SSO.
* When an email with the @qima.com domain is entered, a message is displayed, or the password field is blocked, instructing the user to wait for verification.
* Once verification is complete, the password field is either hidden, and ""Continue"" triggers the Microsoft O365 SSO authentication.
* The functionality works consistently across different regions with varying latencies.
* Implement frontend validation to detect @qima.com email addresses.
* Introduce UI elements (e.g., message display or input blocking) to manage user interaction during the verification process.

* Ensure backend communication with Microsoft O365 API is optimized for quicker response times.",,Vincent Roche,,,,,,,,,,,,,,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@43c9b09,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,"{pullrequest={dataType=pullrequest, state=MERGED, stateCount=1}, json={""cachedValue"":{""errors"":[],""summary"":{""pullrequest"":{""overall"":{""count"":1,""lastUpdated"":""2024-07-23T20:42:57.000+0800"",""stateCount"":1,""state"":""MERGED"",""dataType"":""pullrequest"",""open"":false},""byInstanceType"":{""GitHub"":{""count"":1,""name"":""GitHub""}}}}},""isStale"":true}}",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

Some supervisor accounts that were active over the past 6 months were not correctly migrated. We will force the migration of all accounts with a ROLE_SUPERVISOR that are not deactivated on the QIMAone side.
#* Extract a list of all accounts with the ROLE_SUPERVISOR on QIMAone that are currently active (not deactivated).
#* Check the migration status of these supervisor accounts to determine which accounts have not been migrated to the QIMA Connect user pool.
#* Implement a procedure to force the migration of all identified accounts into the QIMA Connect user pool.
#* Verify that all forced migrations are completed successfully.
#* Ensure that all migrated supervisor accounts can access QIMA Connect without issues.
* A comprehensive list of all active supervisor accounts on QIMAone is generated.
* All supervisor accounts identified as not yet migrated are successfully moved to the QIMA Connect user pool.
* Post-migration, all accounts can log in and function correctly within QIMA Connect.
* Query QIMAone database to identify active ROLE_SUPERVISOR accounts.
* Cross-check these accounts with the QIMA Connect user pool to identify missing migrations.

* Create and execute a migration script or process to move these accounts to QIMA Connect.",,Gabriel Pascual,Vincent Roche,,,,,,,,,,,,,5c3c6b139f443a65fecc24e1,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,,,,,,,,,,,,,;18/Jul/24 10:48 PM;jerome.baumgarten;4500,;22/Jul/24 3:27 PM;gabriel.pascual;21600,,,,,,,,,,0,26100,,,0,26100,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@21498bb8,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,"{pullrequest={dataType=pullrequest, state=MERGED, stateCount=1}, json={""cachedValue"":{""errors"":[],""summary"":{""pullrequest"":{""overall"":{""count"":1,""lastUpdated"":""2024-07-19T17:30:53.000+0800"",""stateCount"":1,""state"":""MERGED"",""dataType"":""pullrequest"",""open"":false},""byInstanceType"":{""GitHub"":{""count"":1,""name"":""GitHub""}}}}},""isStale"":true}}",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Colossal Penguins,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

column1: Disable MFA for all QIMA accounts not identified as individual users.,QID-240,137927,Task,Won't do,QID,QIMA connect,software,Gabriel Pascual,5c3c6b139f443a65fecc24e1,,,N/A,Won't Do,Gabriel Pascual,5c3c6b139f443a65fecc24e1,Vincent Roche,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,Vincent Roche,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,18/Jul/24 6:06 PM,23/Jul/24 9:47 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,23/Jul/24 9:47 PM,,,,,0,qimaone,support,,,,"*Objective:* We need to disable MFA for all QIMA accounts with the following domains: @qima.com, @qimaone.com, and @wqscert.com, which are not recognized by Microsoft O365 as individual users. This will prevent the sending of MFA codes by email for shared accounts that use our application.
#* Build a solution that sends a request to Microsoft O365 for all accounts with the specified domains to check if they are recognized as individual users.
#* If the response from Microsoft O365 indicates that an account is not recognized as an individual user, mark that account for MFA deactivation.
#* Implement a process to remove MFA from all accounts identified as shared (i.e., not recognized as individual users).
* A script or tool is developed to query Microsoft O365 for account recognition status.
* Accounts not recognized as individual users have their MFA settings disabled.
* The solution is tested and verified to ensure that MFA is correctly disabled for all applicable shared accounts.
* Query Microsoft O365 API to check user recognition status.
* Process the response to identify shared accounts.

* Programmatically disable MFA for the identified accounts.",,Vincent Roche,,,,,,,,,,,,,,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,,,,,,,,,,,,,,;22/Jul/24 3:28 PM;gabriel.pascual;21600,,,,,,,,,,,0,21600,,,0,21600,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@24c94dd,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,"{pullrequest={dataType=pullrequest, state=MERGED, stateCount=1}, json={""cachedValue"":{""errors"":[],""summary"":{""pullrequest"":{""overall"":{""count"":1,""lastUpdated"":""2024-07-23T20:19:50.000+0800"",""stateCount"":1,""state"":""MERGED"",""dataType"":""pullrequest"",""open"":false},""byInstanceType"":{""GitHub"":{""count"":1,""name"":""GitHub""}}}}},""isStale"":true}}",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Colossal Penguins,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

column1: I need this data to analyse frequently/important asked questions.
Thank you for giving us more info.
However, we still need approval from your manager to give access to the database. Kindly request approval and share us the email for documentation.

To give you ore context, I want to analyze Freshdesk tickets, and for that, I will use the AIBIME.FRESHDESK_AGENT_DETAILS table. Since I am using Python code to access the database, I need the Oracle URL (PSEUDO/PWD@localhost:11521/AIPROD). Therefore, I need to know my pseudo and password. I'm not sure if I answered all your questions. Please could you show me our to find pseudo and password?
We connect to Oracle Database using a client installed on local instead of a URL.
Could you clarify the following details as well? We need to keep track of these things before we create an account to the database.
# Why access is needed to Oracle Database
# Which Oracle Database do you need access for?
Since Jitesh is OOO, I forward you my demand.
Thanks in advance for the support.
Please could you tell me how to know my password to get access to Qima Oracle database?
I want to get access to aiprod bd using Oracle url. That's why I need my password.

- Remove all CVEs from the .trivyignore file.

column1: [BO] Allow select order charge type multiple times in the dropdown list,SP-18107,137884,Story,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,N/A,,,,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,18/Jul/24 5:11 AM,26/Jul/24 2:03 AM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. Context

Currently, the sales support coordinator needs to indicate discounts individually to comply with GGAP rules and to effectively monitor the discounts provided for the next year. The system currently allows selecting an option only once; after it has been selected, it is not available for selection again.
Imrpove the Order Charge Type dropdown list to allow the user select the options how many times needed
Given I’m logged in the system
When I navigated to Order Charge view
And I click on “Add charge type” button
When I click on the dropdown “Add charge type”
And I select one of the option
Then it must appears in the Order Charge
And the Overall Total must be automatically recalcualte
+When I  click on “Add charge type” button+
+When I click on the dropdown “Add charge type”+
+And I the option selected must be avialable to be selected again+
+Then it must appears in the Order Charge+
Adding the same charge type twice is not possible.

I dont see a reason to add the same charge type twice. This part of the application shares the design with other business like inspection, audits, SASO, etc. and there is a constraint on the database to not allow duplicate charge types on same order.

You can think of creating all the relevant discounts as charge types and then use them in the order",19/Jul/24 4:15 AM;621e0bfca687c5006a5df455;XQ = 5 SPs,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,To Do,18/Jul/24 5:11 AM

Display Auditor Availability in QSP,SP-18105,137882,Epic,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,N/A,,,,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,Magno Bruno Kuwabara,712020:020b2165-51dd-4558-b16f-2d2494eee4c2,18/Jul/24 12:58 AM,18/Jul/24 7:32 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h1. Context

It is important for all QSP users, especially the Scheduling team and the auditors themselves, to be able to check auditor availability. This capability allows them to organize their schedules for upcoming audits and avoid any availability issues that might impact the client.

Currently, dashboards have been created in Tableau by the BI team. These dashboards draw information from the database, displaying audits scheduled through both QIMAcert and the WQS system. However, not all QSP users have access to Tableau due to the high cost of licenses.

Therefore, the strategy is to integrate these dashboards into QSP so that users can access them without requiring additional licenses. This approach is similar to the one developed for Inspection in ACA.

The solution can display auditor availability but cannot block audit dates for the auditors. It was agreed with the business that they would need to block dates in the WQS system if necessary until this feature is improved.

column2: https://dashboards.qima.com/#/workbooks/2103/views] in the home grid of QSP.

column1: #* Provide a button for easy access to the Audit Calendar.
#* Ensure that Auditor Availability is viewable in all necessary views.
#** The display must show only their own audits, using the filter criteria ""Employee Name.""
#* *For Sales, Sales Manager, Coordination, Coordination Manager, Finance, Quality, and Quality Manager Roles*:
#** The display must show all audits and allow users to filter them as needed.
We cannot control the display of information by users / auditors.

If you want to control the display of dashboard by users we will have to create a dashboard for every user which is not possible. Either we have to build this specifically for QIMAcert in case if you are thinking of granular features of controlling the view by auditor, sales, etc.

In case if you have to just display the dashboard for auditor availability (irrespective of roles) in QIMAcert the Xtreme Quote would be 21 points.",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,To Do,18/Jul/24 12:58 AM

In QIMAone, we did this ticket to accept auto-sync documents from QSP to QIMAone: booking’s ADDITIONAL DOCUMENT
And last week, QSP team released this sync feature
* After auto-sync, the operation team went to edit the inspection in QIMAone
* But they got error by clicking SUBMIT button: Invalid input data
* Then they removed all files which have been auto-synced to additional documents, the bookings were submitted successfully

column1: Adjust each target parameter, measure impact on speed and accuracy of responses,AIC-21,137852,Task,In Progress,AIC,AI INSPECTOR CHATBOT,business,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,,,High,,François NOYEZ,5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee,Courtlin Holt-Nguyen,712020:f94edf25-0169-4381-9f2d-bb24ed1d4699,Courtlin Holt-Nguyen,712020:f94edf25-0169-4381-9f2d-bb24ed1d4699,17/Jul/24 4:55 PM,24/Jul/24 1:12 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,24/Jul/24 12:00 AM,0,,,,,,"* *Average Response Time (ART):* The average time it takes for the chatbot to respond after a user sends a message. This helps assess how quickly the chatbot can process and reply to user inputs.
* *First Response Time (FRT):* The time taken to send the first response to a user's initial query. This is crucial for setting the tone of the interaction and user satisfaction.

* *Time to Resolution (TTR):* The total time taken to resolve a user's issue or complete a conversation. This measures the efficiency of the chatbot in handling complete interactions.",,Calvin Marshall,Courtlin Holt-Nguyen,François NOYEZ,Marius Kwémou,,,,,,,,,,,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,712020:f94edf25-0169-4381-9f2d-bb24ed1d4699,5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee,613041b5ae44ae0070c3c53a,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,AIC-20,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@aa76d8,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,0

column1: * *Average Response Time (ART):* The average time it takes for the chatbot to respond after a user sends a message. This helps assess how quickly the chatbot can process and reply to user inputs.
* *First Response Time (FRT):* The time taken to send the first response to a user's initial query. This is crucial for setting the tone of the interaction and user satisfaction.

* *Time to Resolution (TTR):* The total time taken to resolve a user's issue or complete a conversation. This measures the efficiency of the chatbot in handling complete interactions.",19/Jul/24 4:44 PM;613041b5ae44ae0070c3c53a;[~accountid:712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552] The most important metrics to measure are ATR and TTR ( average ).,19/Jul/24 5:02 PM;712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552;[~accountid:613041b5ae44ae0070c3c53a] ok and do you have the ability to monitor these on the backend?,19/Jul/24 11:38 PM;613041b5ae44ae0070c3c53a;Yes it is possible.,"20/Jul/24 8:59 AM;712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552;[~accountid:613041b5ae44ae0070c3c53a] ok so more precisely, can we monitor these metrics right now or would you need time to develop a monitoring apparatus?","23/Jul/24 4:12 PM;712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552;Hi [~accountid:5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee]  I wasn’t able to get an answer from Marius before he went on leave, but before we make any changes, I am wondering what we can do to monitor speed. Are there any metrics we can get from back end?","24/Jul/24 1:03 AM;5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee;Hi [~accountid:712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552]

As far as I can see for now, there does not seem to be in the project tools or functionalities dedicated to measuring the time needed for the chatbot to answer to a message posted by the user. In which case we would need to design ourselves the software architecture needed to do that (maybe we could reuse potential DB resources already needed by the project?) and perform the needed devs ourselves.","24/Jul/24 11:46 AM;712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552;Hi [~accountid:5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee] noted that we don’t have project tools to track time. At the current moment, I have not heard any complaints concerning the speed. If we have significant number of complaints, then we can play with the parameters to see if any setting would help increase speed. As of this moment, let's put this on the back burner.

Objective:
Implement Appcues user sentiment capture within our application.
#** *Product Score:* Utilize a 1-5 Likert scale to rate the product.
#** *Free Text Comment Section:* Allow users to provide suggestions and additional comments.
* Efficient capture of both quantitative and qualitative user sentiments.
* Integration of a user-friendly interface for feedback submission.
* Collaborate with the NoCode team to integrate Appcues for sentiment capture.
* Ensure the feedback forms are easy to navigate and submit.

Direct Links to Reference Documents (GIs, booking),AIC-13,137844,Task,In Progress,AIC,AI INSPECTOR CHATBOT,business,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,,,Highest,,François NOYEZ,5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,17/Jul/24 4:49 PM,23/Jul/24 11:49 AM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,26/Jul/24 12:00 AM,0,,,,,,"h4. Objective:
Provide a direct hyperlink to a reference document and extract the following details:
# A snippet of the relevant text.
# The page number where the relevant information is located.
# The line number of the relevant information on that page.
#* Create a direct hyperlink to the reference document (GIs, booking).
#* Fetch a snippet of the relevant text from the document.
#* Identify the page number where the relevant information is located.
#* Determine the line number of where the relevant information can be found on the page.
* *Snippet:* ""This is an example snippet of the relevant text.""

This ticket is a prerequisite for the testing team to be able to provide accuracy % per each GI file. After this is implemented, the testing team will be able to report on GI accuracy and identify deficiencies in the documents + make a workorder task for the protocol team to make an update to the identified GI doc if needed.
In the interim, the testing team will report accuracy figures at the client level. ",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,137231,Enhancements,In Progress,17/Jul/24 4:57 PM

Since the creation is estimated to take in excess of one month, we will move forward with the creation of a new microservice in QIMAworkspace, which should take significantly less time to implement.
* *Alternative Solution:* Develop a new microservice within QIMAworkspace.
* *Entry Point:* Single sign-on (SSO) for all QIMA employees.
* Create new icon and welcome message.
* Identify which FE resource can help create this new entry.

FYI, since the data team will need more than a month to implement a new plugin, we have decided to create a new micro-service in QIMAworkspace which will be significantly faster to implement. We will need your assistance with arranging Front-End (FE) resources to make this happen. Can you please advise which team/specific personnel can be approached for this task?

In the interim, I need your help to design a simple icon for the new micro-service. We can name it ""Inspection-GPT,"" and the info text can read: ""AI-powered chatbot focused on enhancing inspection efficiency.""
Could you please help confirm the web address we should point to for this new micro-service?

[AIMS][Program] Add the settings to predefine the report company and address in the Program,SP-18092,137833,Story,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,Medium,,,,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,17/Jul/24 11:23 AM,22/Jul/24 11:13 AM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. User story
I want to customize the report company name and company address per program level
So that it can make sure the correct company name and address can show on the report
* Add the field “Report Company Name” and “Report Company Address”

** Reason: Currently we are capturing the report company name and address from QIMA Customer, and show it on the report. But the SIC may not update the data on time or the company may have the unique company name per program.
** The data set in the Program should sync to the order level
*** If no data set in the Program, we should follow the previous logic by capturing the QIMA Customer data
When he inputs the report company name and address which is different from QIMA Customer

Then he can see the report company name and address on the report following the logic set in the Program",,Suki Yuan,,,,,,,,,,,,,,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,22/Jul/24 11:13 AM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240722-031042.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236073,22/Jul/24 11:13 AM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240722-031108.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236075,22/Jul/24 11:13 AM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240722-031213.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236074,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@38459642,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-17573,[LT] Client's Specific Requirement Functions for Email and Report File Names,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

This feature is for CONSUMER GOODS / PRODUCE, NOT for CONSUMER GOOD / PRODUCE

- If the value is too long, we display it with a maximum of 1 line, then display ""…"" with a tooltip

- If there is no corresponding value, we display ""---""
In case of a new email, PM needs to add it to this confluence page and the template needs to be validated by the marketing team before development.

PM needs to update the confluence page with new permission

When we deploy a new QIMAone release, we have an ad-hoc maintenance page when a user accesses QIMAone. But if he is already connected to QIMAone, he won’t notice anything until he does an action that calls the API and this may not be a good UX.
What about a mechanism both on the infra and front sides to handle such case and let the user know that the API is unavailable during this scheduled maintenance?

[2024 Q3] [Tech] Enhance cypress automation testing for AIMS,SP-18073,137698,Epic,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,N/A,,Dod Du,5fa1059771ab9e006a145c19,Dod Du,5fa1059771ab9e006a145c19,Dod Du,5fa1059771ab9e006a145c19,15/Jul/24 2:46 PM,25/Jul/24 3:24 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"Currently, our regression automation testing has low coverage, and performing weekly manual regression testing is time-consuming for QA. Consequently, when we introduce new features or refactor existing ones, some bugs end up in the production environment.
To prevent this from happening, we must improve the coverage of automation testing in our LT applications.

Given the extensive number of test cases required, relying solely on a single QA would significantly slow progress. Therefore, we need developers to assist in writing automation tests using Cypress. This collaboration will allow us to quickly build automated test cases and enhance the coverage of QSP regression through automation.",,Automation for Jira,Dod Du,,,,,,,,,,,,,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,5fa1059771ab9e006a145c19,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@2a40f01,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,ghx-label-14,,,,To Do,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

column1: I want to add the INLINE inspection option under DUPRO booking,
So that client / sales is able to book this new service.
** Add a new field with two options
“Standard DUPRO: During Production Inspection, is a quality control process conducted in the middle of a production cycle.
Inline inspection: An inline inspection refers to a quality control process conducted directly on the production line while the product is being manufactured.”
* Able to place order + edit booking in ACA
* For the previous pending orders, auto fill the value “During Production Inspection type“
Given that I am a client, when I book DURPO type that I can be able to see the new field with 2 options.

Given that I am a client, when I look at the previous pending DURPO orders that I can see the data being auto filled with “Standard DUPRO”.",,Automation for Jira,Eric Context
Operations has reported an issue to confirm allocation.
It has started after last release in production.
*Given* I am logged in with Coordination / Coordination Manager / Admin roles
*And* I have an order in the ""Waiting for Allocation"" status
*And* I have confirmed the audit date, allocated auditors, and assigned roles
*When* I click on the ""Confirm Allocation"" button
*Then* a new modal to select/add recipients pops up
+*And*+ +the order does not move to the next step+
*Given* I am logged in with Coordination / Coordination Manager / Admin roles
*And* I have an order in the ""Waiting for Allocation"" status
*And* I have confirmed the audit date, allocated auditors, and assigned roles
*When* I click on the ""Confirm Allocation"" button
*Then* a new modal to select/add recipients pops up
+*And*+ +the email is sent to the recipients+
This order had Certifying Body as empty due to which it was confirming.
For existing orders which are beyond waiting for validation, we have to either update this information for all the orders where it is missing.

For this , I updated CB and WQS LLC and confirmed allocation and it worked",15/Jul/24 4:52 PM;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;[~accountid:] Please log the time spent on this ticket!,15/Jul/24 4:52 PM;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;[~accountid:60126101b7bda90068a25087] Please log the time spent on this ticket!,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Done,15/Jul/24 4:52 PM

QIMAone - Extract report data for VF,BUS-507,137666,Story,In Progress,BUS,Business Intelligence ,software,Antoine Chapelet,557058:faf1dca1-f7c9-4a72-b701-fdd0c0b11984,,,High,,Antoine Chapelet,557058:faf1dca1-f7c9-4a72-b701-fdd0c0b11984,Rioual Pierre,5c9aef3954b7300555f719a5,Rioual Pierre,5c9aef3954b7300555f719a5,12/Jul/24 7:20 PM,26/Jul/24 6:46 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,support,,,,,"{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
Update : BI team is doing by using tableau
On QSP, VF used to have an API from QSP to their platform to transfer report data.
Once migrated to QIMAone, they stopped receiving the data on their platform as we did not had the API.
On the long run this won't be needed as we are performing inspection on both QIMAOne and VF platform directly.
Get an extract of QIMAOne containing all information needed by VF
It should follow the same format as VF used to review
Warning -> R-Cloud and product name have to be into 2 different fields
Fist extract:  we would need to get all historical data since the migration of VF in QIMAone = 15 nov 2023.
-VF is implementing their own platform called INFOR
When we do inspection for a Brand already in INFOR, our inspector would do report in both:
-QIMAone - to keep some data for benchmark + for inspectors monitoring
On such cases, client would have access to the data.
When we do inspection for brand not yet in INFOR, would inspector would only do report on QIMAone
For those cases, as client don't have INFOR, they need your help to consolidate the data for their reporting.
-Reporting could be done on a weekly or monthly basis

-Eventually all brands should be on INFOR - This may happen in 6 months, 1 year or later - I tried to challenge KA and sales without success.",,Adam Michalak,Antoine Chapelet,Automation for Jira,Nan Chen,Rioual Pierre,,,,,,,,,,61e654cfeb1fb600719af3f6,557058:faf1dca1-f7c9-4a72-b701-fdd0c0b11984,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f,5c9aef3954b7300555f719a5,,,,,,,,,,;17/Jul/24 5:57 PM;nan.chen;7200,,,,,,,,,,,0,7200,,,0,7200,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,12/Jul/24 7:19 PM;pierre.rioual;download (5).png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234833,26/Jul/24 10:25 AM;achapelet;image-20240726-022319.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236983,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@64c9165c,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

column1: [AIMS][Program] Add the settings to customize the notification email subject in the Program,SP-18052,137664,Story,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,,,,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,12/Jul/24 6:33 PM,17/Jul/24 7:36 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. User story
I want to customize the test report email subject and test report file name
So that I can quickly identify the email and report
* Update the layout for the “Notification” page
* If “Disable” is selected, no need to block sending the email
*** The user enters a special subject in the input field.
*** The system saves the special subject and the user’s choice to send notifications.
** *Outcome:* Notifications are sent with the specified special subject.
** *Trigger:* The user selects the “Enable” option and leaves the special subject field blank.
*** The system saves users' choice to send notifications without a special subject.
** *Outcome:* Notifications are sent with a default subject.
*** The system saves the user’s choice to disable notifications.
** *Outcome:* Notifications for test reports are disabled.
** *Trigger:* The user toggles between the ""Enable"" and ""Disable"" options.
*** The system updates the user's preference based on the latest selection.
** *Outcome:* The notification settings are updated accordingly and applied immediately.
# The user can choose to enable or disable notifications for the notifications
# If the user chooses to enable notifications, they can optionally specify a special subject for the notification.
# If the user does not specify a special subject, the system will use a default subject.

# Only one option (Send or Disable) can be selected at a time.",,Suki Yuan,,,,,,,,,,,,,,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-18051,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,12/Jul/24 6:33 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240712-100603.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234829,12/Jul/24 6:33 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240712-101004.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234830,15/Jul/24 10:24 AM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240715-022416.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234858,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@51c35384,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-17573,[LT] Client's Specific Requirement Functions for Email and Report File Names,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

User story
I want to customize the test report email subject and test report file name
So that I can quickly identify the email and report
* Add the field “Special Title for Test Report File Name”
** Add the note to share an example for the users
** Priority: Program setting < Report generation: 在program这里可以预设逻辑，但是在生成报告的页面自动带出来file name后，也要允许用户在Report generation的popup修改

column1: What: The telephone number doesn't match the selected country in the address details.
- Inspections IDs, Products IDs, POs etc:
- Can support team directly contact this user? YES
1.Go to Lexelart Brand in QIMAone Platform
3.Search ""FINE CHEMICAL VIETNAM"" in the Main Identifier
5.Scroll down to locate the Work and Home Phone Number
6.Then, you'll see that the system automatically selects Afghanistan as the country code.

Normally, it should be on the country code that the user selected. For example: The user selects Vietnam and it should be still Vietnam when he/she checks or view it again. But the system automatically selects Afghanistan as the country code, as if it's the default.
For example: The user selects Vietnam and it should be still Vietnam when he/she checks or view it again. But the system automatically selects Afghanistan as the country code, as if it's the default.
Change the Telephone Country code manually when editing the information.

column2: i0g267:,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,0%,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,LIMSPP,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"11/Jul/24 9:52 PM;5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8;[~accountid:712020:fe5f6ce0-6fd6-4697-aea5-7567250e97a2] , the phone country code is not affected by the Address Country.  You can have Address in Vietnam but have a Phone number in another country.   In this case, the entity was imported without Country Code in Phone number that is why the Default country code is selected when Editing it.  If you put country code in the import entity csv file, it will be auto-selected when you Edit the entity.  So here, if you select Vietnam country in Phone and save it, it will be auto-selected to Vietnam code the next time you edit it.

column1: To avoid this, make sure you have country code in the Import entity CSV file.

column1: After check code logic in PSI make report available, I found there has two “Make Report available to Client“ button in PSI order page.
Another is in “Report Cover & Bonus“ page

There is a setting in customer to control where to display. And if click “Make Report available to Client“ button in “*Report Cover & Bonus*“ page, REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON in the ORDER_PROD_REPORT table will be null. Because in this case, PSI does not save the time into REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON field.

And I wrote a SQL to check how many finished orders REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON is null. The data in this Excel is for report submit time in 2024. Over 5,000 reports, I don't know if this is a bug or a feature. 😆
ogi.ORDER_ID, ogi.ORDER_NUMBER, ogi.SERVICE_TYPE, op.PRODUCT_ID, ogi.ACTUAL_INSP_DATE, ogi.ORDER_PLACER, cc.COMPANY_NAME, opr.REPORT_SUBMIT_TIME
left join ORDER_PRODUCT op on op.ORDER_ID = ogi.ORDER_ID
left join ORDER_PROD_REPORT opr on opr.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID
left join CRM_COMPANY cc on cc.ID = ogi.COMPANY_ID
I just found another table also has “REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON“ field.

And if the customer settings “Make report available to client“ is “Per order“, click “make report available“ button will update date in this table. Otherwise both tables will be updated at the same time.","24/Jul/24 4:40 PM;619dbe81b0b630006abd8fc7;h2. QA Note:
fix: the column REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON in the ORDER_PROD_REPORT table null
h3. Section Testing Suggestion(s) for QA to test:
# Set the customer settings “Make report available to client“ is “Per order“.
# Use this cusetomer create an order and finish it.
# Click ”Make Reports available to Client” button in “Report Cover & Bonus“ page.
# Use sql to check if column is null.
{noformat}select PRODUCT_ID, REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON from ORDER_PROD_REPORT where PRODUCT_ID = 'xxx';{noformat}

column3: Before Make report available to client, it’s empty in the table for the data
column6: After Make report available to client, it’s not empty in the table for the data

column1: posted in QIMAtech / platform-qimaone-support on Thursday, July 11, 2024 11:53 AM
No issue found by [~accountid:625f6c01b8be7c006a44b8d8] on the server performance.
Please read below email from KIK - can you look into the underlying issue and come up with a quick robust resolution to this?
KIK is a Key Account both for QIMAone & QIMA, generating >USD1M, and much more potential to grow, so please let's ensure we resolve this swiftly.
In copy the CSM in charge Alice & Karla, in case of any questions.
{color:#ffffff}*Subject:*{color}{color:#ffffff} Escalation of QimaOne Platform Performance Issues{color}
I am writing to bring to your attention a significant decrease in the performance of the QimaOne platform over the past two weeks.

We have observed that page loading times have been progressively increasing, particularly towards the end of the workweek (Thursday and Friday) when we are creating inspections for the following week.
Last Friday, the lag time reached approximately two minutes. Despite reaching out to Support, who suggested clearing browsing history and cookies, changing browsers, etc., the issue persists.
While these actions provided a temporary improvement for creating 3 to 5 new inspections, the performance quickly degraded, resulting in page load times ranging from 30 seconds to 2 minutes.
Since Monday, a colleague has been assisting with creating and editing inspections on a fresh device with no prior platform cookies.

Despite this, the slowdown reoccurred within a few hours. This issue affects not only the “new inspection” workflow but also other menus, such as the Assignments, Reports, and Products & POs main pages, all of which take excessively long (up to 2 minutes) to load.
Both the .com and .cn URLs are equally affected.
We discussed this issue yesterday with Alice and Zoe from Support, Product Manager Nan Chen, and Dev Team member Jocelyn Bernales.
Although they have promised to investigate and optimize the platform, they mentioned not seeing any issues on their end and requested our assistance in troubleshooting to identify the root cause.
Unfortunately, we do not have the bandwidth for extensive troubleshooting at this time.

Given the current performance issues, which are particularly critical now as both Eva’s team and mine are adding inspections to the platform, I am escalating this matter in hopes of expediting the resolution.

I would like to suggest that a member of your Support or Development team visit our office to recreate our environment as closely as possible to test and diagnose the issue, or let me know if you have any other proposal?
Thank you for your immediate attention to this matter. I look forward to your prompt response and resolution.
{color:#ffffff}Mit freundlichen Grüssen/ 祝好/ Best Regards{color}

column1: [eFiling] 3 - Add CPSC eFiling fields in order details page,SP-18019,137394,Story,In Progress,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,,Alexandra,712020:e9b5f465-6a91-47d2-ab74-271f627741b8,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,10/Jul/24 6:25 PM,25/Jul/24 4:27 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. User story
I want to add the fields for CPSC eFiling
So that I can send the data to CPSC
* Product ID type: This field should sync from the account level and allow to update in the order level
** SKU → If selected, then no need to show additional field below
** GTIN → If selected, then need to show additional field below to input the number
** Model number → If selected, then need to show additional field below to input the number
** Serial number → If selected, then need to show additional field below to input the number
** UPC → If selected, then need to show additional field below to input the number
** Registered number → If selected, then need to show additional field below to input the number
** Alternate ID → If selected, then need to show additional field below to input the number
* Manufacture date: date format → Allow to select the past date
*Factory details: Have a text box for auto parsing → Allow the user to edit*
* Country: Dropdown list → Use QIMA GEO data
Question: 可以用下面的组件吗？

column1: [BO] Allow user to arrange the sequence of columns on the order/home grid,SP-18018,137393,Story,Code Review,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,Medium,,Claudio Luis Cristiano Coelho,712020:e80d8f2c-5b0d-45c6-b3c7-4e4b024082b2,Binesh,60126101b7bda90068a25087,Binesh,60126101b7bda90068a25087,10/Jul/24 5:38 PM,15/Jul/24 8:28 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h3. Use case
I should be able to arrange to sequence of columns on the order grid and save it
so that even during next login it should retain the sequence

The importance and the sequence of the data point displayed on the grid is different for different roles. Users who schedule the audit would be more keen to see the audit dates, certificate type and auditors assigned, where as technical manager would be interested in certificate type, products involved.
This feature would allow the business users arrange the sequence of columns as per their need and save it and every login the sequence would be retained.
