User story
I want to update the test list format on the ACA
So that it can make sure the data is consistent between the quotation pdf and ACA test list
* Currently the pdf quotation’s discount data is inconsistent with what the client can see in the ACA
* To fix the root cause, we need to update the ACA test list following our latest template guideline:
1/ Update the title name from ""Discount"" to ""Special instruction“
3/ If there is no ""Special price""/""FOC""/""Discount"", we should put ""-""
* Note: Remember to deploy for Inquiry’s quotation and Booking’s quotation
** 如果在program配置special price，算是net price，应该在quotation/invoice显示“Special price”
** 或者，如果在test management单独配置net price而没有在program配置，也应该在quotation/invoice显示“Special price”
When he received the quotation email

He can see the ""Special price""/""FOC""/""Discount"" under the “Special instruction” column and the data is consistent with pdf quotation",,Albert huang,Automation for Jira,Mark Cai,Suki Bug After Delete Group Report,PL-22517,137390,Bug,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,Medium,,,,Rodrigo Morales,611adec4e05b7b006ade866c,Rodrigo Morales,611adec4e05b7b006ade866c,10/Jul/24 4:57 PM,17/Jul/24 5:18 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,customer,support,,,,"Sometimes supervisors assign the same inspection to more than one group inspection and then the report list in QIMAOne looks like this:
In this case, the inspection ID 677632 is part of 2 group reports (12283 and 12286) and this is obviously an error, so the supervisor should delete one of the group reports.
In the above example, the supervisor has already deleted group report 12283, but the list of reports still shows that the inspections are part of 2 group reports.
When we click on the group report 12283, we get the message ""This page does not exist:

To fix this problem, what we do is open the group that is not deleted (in this case: 12286) and update the group, enter to ""Add Inspection"" and then click on Update Group; doing that the report list no longer shows the group already deleted (12283).
Please see the following video for more details:
- User type: Team user or Inspector
- Inspections IDs, Products IDs, POs etc:
- Happening time: (Specify if it's user's local time or French time)
- Can support team directly contact this user? YES/NO
- If yes, user's contact: (Email address for example)
Issue is created by (PR or Jira ticket link):
(Enter here in which environment(s) this problem happened)
(Enter any other details such as examples, links to requirements, etc. Any criteria that might help with fixing the problem. Attach screenshots if possible. More detail is better)
(If there is a way to work around the problem, place that information here)
- Link to Figma Dashboard /Figma Style Guide to respect guidelines
- API documentation filled in case of Public API (Swagger/Redoc)

column1: *Commun part* for *CSM* or *PM* who creates a business enabler ticket
We need to know when was the accounts added to the QIMAone platform for Invoice purposes.

If you have any suggestions, please put them here
This feature is for CONSUMER GOODS / PRODUCE, NOT for CONSUMER GOOD / PRODUCE
Put UI link here (*NOT* UX sandbox screens)
Modify this part if it doesn't fit your US
- If the value is too long, we display it with a maximum of 1 line, then display ""…"" with a tooltip
- If the value is one single long word, we need to cut it to fit into the component
- If there is no corresponding value, we display ""---""
In case of a new email, PM needs to add it to this confluence page and the template needs to be validated by the marketing team before development.
*Important remark: NOTIFUS will be out of service end of 2023, so please don't implement new email with NOTIFUS until we find a new external service*

If It's a *new permission for BRAND team user*, we MUST display this permission into QIMAone: settings/role/backoffice-user. Please respect permissions' order as in the confluence page.

User story
I want to keep the original order rather than canceling it and creating a new one
So that it can ensure the data is correct (There are too much cancelled orders)
* Currently, when we transfer the office site, the existing order will be canceled and a new order will be created → mess-up the volume analysis
* Expectedly, we should keep one order only and update the office code. For example, “T-24075110-15-R” should be updated to “T-24075110-14-R”

column1: [Security][PSI][Audit][Certificate][Inquiry] Hide the client's contact and add the button to unlock,SP-17999,137338,Story,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,,,,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM,17/Jul/24 7:37 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. User story
I want to auto-mask the client’s contact in PSI and Inquiry and add the button to unmask
So that I can track who and when to get the client’s contact
* Scope: PSI, Audit, Certificate and Inquiry
* Auto mask the following information for all roles
** Once click the button, auto show all the masked information
** After the information is shown, then hide this button
* Logs will be enabled for users who ‘clicked’ on the button, displaying customer information
** Logs should be kept for at least *30 days*
Given the users in PSI, Audit, Certificate and Inquiry
When he/she check the above page

He/She will find the contact information is hidden and there is a button to click",,Suki Yuan,,,,,,,,,,,,,,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-17980,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-111051.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234218,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-111429.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234219,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-111555.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234220,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-111921.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234221,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-112054.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234222,09/Jul/24 4:28 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-112318.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234223,09/Jul/24 4:43 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240709-083822.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234232,09/Jul/24 4:43 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240709-084109.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234231,09/Jul/24 4:43 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240709-084249.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234233,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@4c48645a,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-17979,[Security] QIMA Customer security improvements,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

ArgoCD: need to "hard refresh",DEVOPS-3146,137333,Bug,In Progress,DEVOPS,TechOps,software,Guillaume Camus,5c04f022e91d16692a39f348,,,N/A,,Guillaume Camus,5c04f022e91d16692a39f348,Lois Facchetti,5e844a825b08780c1c3cb14c,Lois Facchetti,5e844a825b08780c1c3cb14c,09/Jul/24 12:10 PM,24/Jul/24 11:48 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"+Description:+
Since last argocd upgrade, there are some issues with the refresh, which +sometimes+ happen:
* if no auto-sync: need to “hard refresh” to see all the changes.
* if auto-sync: need to “hard refresh” for the app to automatically sync!!! → very dangerous
Let’s fix this one, here are an ideas from our private chat:

column3: smart-link]  which is responsible of the cache management.

column1: `argocd-repo-server` Command Reference - Argo CD - Declarative GitOps CD for Kubernetes
We could increase the {{parallelismlimit}} and reduce {{revision-cache-expiration duration}}

User story
I want to auto-mask the client’s contact in QIMA Customer and add the button to unmask
So that I can track who and when to get the client’s contact
* Auto mask the following information for all roles
* Add the button of “+Show contact info+”
** Once click the button, auto show all the masked information
** After the information is shown, then hide this button
* Logs will be enabled for users who ‘clicked’ on the button, displaying customer information
** Logs should be kept for at least *30 days*
For the QIMA Customer detailed page, once click the button, only the current page’s information will auto-show → The user must click the button on every page.
Given the users in QIMA Customer
When he/she check the above page

He/She will find the contact information is hidden and there is a button to click",,Suki Yuan,,,,,,,,,,,,,,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-17999,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,08/Jul/24 7:27 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-111051.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/233991,08/Jul/24 7:27 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-111429.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/233987,09/Jul/24 4:57 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240709-085555.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234245,09/Jul/24 4:57 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240709-085632.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/234244,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@7f3b45f0,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,,SP-17979,[Security] QIMA Customer security improvements,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

[Security] QIMA Customer security improvements,SP-17979,137306,Epic,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,,,,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,Suki Yuan,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,08/Jul/24 6:19 PM,22/Jul/24 3:36 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"h2. PRD: [https://qima.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/IT/pages/edit-v2/3317137518
* To define where QIMA customer confidential information are displayed and stored.
* To strengthen security controls applied in QSP.
* To implement least privilege access control on the system.
* To mask QIMA customer confidential information on display.
* To implement user logging activities on the system.
* To prevent and minimize malicious and unintentional insider threats.
h2. Proposed changes (details in the file attached):
* Masking of customer email address and mobile number on display and as default
** A button will be available for users to click and display complete customer information. Logs will be kept for 30 days
* Implement password expiry for QIMA users every 90 days
h2. Task 1: Mask client’s contact in QIMA Customer, PSI, Audit, Certificate, Inquiry and QCore service
Mask the display of customer email addresses and mobile numbers by default, with an option for authorized users to view the complete information. Log these views for audit purposes
*I want* customer email addresses and mobile numbers to be masked by default, with an option to view the complete information
*So that* customer confidential information is protected and access to it is logged for security purposes
#* Customer email addresses and mobile numbers should be masked by default across the scope
#* There should be a button or link that authorized users can click to view the full customer contact information
#* Once clicked, the complete information should be displayed for *20 seconds* (After 20 seconds, the information will be auto-masked again)
#* Every time the button is clicked to view full customer contact information, the event should be logged with the user’s ID, timestamp, and the specific customer information viewed
#* Logs should be retained for 30 days
The prototype below is designed by considering the balance between security requirements and user experience
+QIMA Customer (The same button will add to the scope mentioned above)+
h2. Task 2: Implement password expiry for QIMA users every 90 days
*Title:* Implement Password Expiry for QIMA Users Every 90 Days
*As a* QIMA user, *I want* my password to expire every 90 days *so that* my account remains secure and compliant with security best practices.
# Users are notified 15 days, and 7 days before their password expires.
# Users are forced to change their password upon login if it has expired.
# Users are prompted with a friendly message explaining why their password needs to be changed.
# The system keeps a log of password changes for audit purposes.
# Users receive an immediate email confirmation upon successfully changing their password.
#* *Trigger:* 15 days before the password is due to expire.
#** Send an email notification to the user.
#* *Outcome:* User is aware of the upcoming password expiry.
#* *Trigger:* 7 days before the password is due to expire.
#** Send a reminder email notification to the user.
#* *Outcome:* User is reminded of the impending password expiry.
#* *Trigger:* User tries to log in after their password expiration date.
#** Display a message prompting the user to change their password.
#* *Outcome:* User is forced to update their password to gain access.
#* *Trigger:* User opts to change their password before it expires.
#** User navigates to the password change section.
#** User inputs current password and new password.
#** System checks if the new password meets security criteria.
#* *Outcome:* User successfully changes their password and the 90-day counter resets.
#** Send a confirmation email to the user.
#* *Outcome:* User receives confirmation that their password has been changed.
#* *Trigger:* An event related to password changes occurs (e.g., a user changes their password).
#** Log the event with a timestamp and relevant user information.
#* *Outcome:* A secure and auditable record of password changes is maintained.
# Develop notification system for expiry warnings.
# Integrate password change flow with security checks (no reuse, etc.).

# Implement confirmation email system.",,Suki Yuan,,,,,,,,,,,,,,6164edac72f6970069baeb13,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,08/Jul/24 6:35 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;QIMA Security Improvements.pdf;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/233983,08/Jul/24 7:32 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240708-113131.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/233992,22/Jul/24 3:35 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240722-073412.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236179,22/Jul/24 3:35 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240722-073427.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236177,22/Jul/24 3:35 PM;ug:1b9dc9c7-0eec-4b47-ba8e-5f1a22874a6a;image-20240722-073447.png;https://qima.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/236178,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@5f5f62a5,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,PROD,,,ghx-label-5,,,[Security] QIMA Customer security improvements,To Do,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

column1: Incorrect display of label information for mixed samples,QL-3692,137299,Story,Done,QL,QIMAlabs,software,Tony Law,5d721c5234b3d20d97783470,"LabVantage EAR Build: 0850.382.01

LabVantage Release: 8.5.1",https://lims.qima.com,Highest,,Hydie Chan,628a5f6cd5ec4f0069e6ce7e,luca.chen,712020:b7ea4ce2-168a-47a7-b5cc-dad326ab2721,luca.chen,712020:b7ea4ce2-168a-47a7-b5cc-dad326ab2721,08/Jul/24 5:06 PM,09/Jul/24 5:35 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,Chemical,HZ,,,,"LIMS PROD >> Sample Id: T2406978911R-C001,Samples are mixed in the sample label and the sample information is indicated incorrectly.
* The correct value for the contents of the red box 1 (1R-M+1R-M) is ""M001+M002"".
* The mass data corresponding to (M001/M002) needs to be captured in red box 2.
select distinct S_Sample.S_SampleID as sampleID , workitem.u_methodshortname as methodShortName,
(select listagg(substr(s_sampleid,*instr(s_sampleid,'-')+1,4*), '+') within group (order by s_sampleid) from s_childsample where s_childsampleid = s_sample.s_sampleid) material,
(select listagg(sdidataitem.displayvalue,' + ') within group (order by sdidataitem.keyid1, sdidataitem.displayvalue) from sdidata
left join sdidataitem on sdidataitem.sdcid = sdidata.sdcid and sdidataitem.keyid1 = sdidata.keyid1 and sdidataitem.keyid2 = sdidata.keyid2 and sdidataitem.keyid3 = sdidata.keyid3

and sdidataitem.paramlistid = sdidata.paramlistid and sdidataitem.paramlistversionid = sdidata.paramlistversionid and sdidataitem.variantid = sdidata.variantid and sdidataitem.dataset = sdidata.dataset
left join S_CHILDSAMPLE on sdidataitem.keyid1 = S_CHILDSAMPLE.S_SAMPLEID
where sdidata.SDCID = sdidataitem.SDCID and sdidata.SDCID = 'Sample' and sdidataitem.paramid = 'SampleMass'
and sdidata.sourceworkitemid  in ( select distinct sourceworkitemid  from  sdidata s inner join workitem w on sourceworkitemid = w.workitemid
NVL((  Case when   workitem.u_methodshortname = 'THM'  then (select distinct  'N' from sdiworkitem sw where sw.sdcid = 'Sample'  and sw.keyid1  = S_Sample.S_SampleID
and exists (select 1 from  workitem w  where sdcid = 'Sample' and  sw.workitemid = w.workitemid and w.U_METHODSHORTNAME = 'THM (Screening)'))
when workitem.u_methodshortname = 'SHM' then (select distinct 'N' from sdiworkitem sw where sw.sdcid = 'Sample'  and sw.keyid1  = S_Sample.S_SampleID
and exists (select 1 from  workitem w  where sdcid = 'Sample' and  sw.workitemid = w.workitemid and w.U_METHODSHORTNAME in ( 'SHM-19E', 'SHM-8E')))
when workitem.u_methodshortname = 'SHM-8E' then (select distinct 'N' from sdiworkitem sw where sw.sdcid = 'Sample'  and sw.keyid1  = S_Sample.S_SampleID
and exists (select 1 from  workitem w  where sdcid = 'Sample' and  sw.workitemid = w.workitemid and w.U_METHODSHORTNAME in ( 'SHM-19E')))
left join s_request on s_request.s_requestid = S_Sample.REQUESTID
left join u_orderstatus on u_orderstatus.requestid = s_request.s_requestid
left join sdiworkitem on sdiworkitem.keyid1 = S_Sample.S_SampleID and sdiworkitem.SDCID = 'Sample' and workitemTypeFlag = 'P'
left join workitem on sdiworkitem.WorkitemID = workitem.WorkitemID
left join (select sdidata.keyid1, workitem.U_METHODSHORTNAME, max(sdidataitem.displayvalue) as displayvalue, max(sdidataitem.displayunits) as displayunits
inner join workitem on sdidata.sourceworkitemid = workitem.WorkitemID
left join sdidataitem on sdidataitem.sdcid = sdidata.sdcid and sdidataitem.keyid1 = sdidata.keyid1 and sdidataitem.keyid2 = sdidata.keyid2 and sdidataitem.keyid3 = sdidata.keyid3

and sdidataitem.paramlistid = sdidata.paramlistid and sdidataitem.paramlistversionid = sdidata.paramlistversionid and sdidataitem.variantid = sdidata.variantid and sdidataitem.dataset = sdidata.dataset
group by sdidata.keyid1,workitem.U_METHODSHORTNAME) displayValueUnit on displayValueUnit.keyid1 = S_Sample.S_SampleID and displayValueUnit.U_METHODSHORTNAME = workitem.U_METHODSHORTNAME
left join (select sdidata.keyid1, workitem.U_METHODSHORTNAME, sdidataitem.paramid, sdidataitem.ALIASID, max(sdidataitem.displayvalue) as displayvalue, max(sdidataitem.displayunits) as displayunits
inner join workitem on sdidata.sourceworkitemid = workitem.WorkitemID
left join sdidataitem on sdidataitem.sdcid = sdidata.sdcid and sdidataitem.keyid1 = sdidata.keyid1 and sdidataitem.keyid2 = sdidata.keyid2 and sdidataitem.keyid3 = sdidata.keyid3

and sdidataitem.paramlistid = sdidata.paramlistid and sdidataitem.paramlistversionid = sdidata.paramlistversionid and sdidataitem.variantid = sdidata.variantid and sdidataitem.dataset = sdidata.dataset
group by sdidata.keyid1, workitem.U_METHODSHORTNAME, sdidataitem.paramid , sdidataitem.ALIASID
order by sdidataitem.paramid) displayValueUnit_PH on displayValueUnit_PH.keyid1 = S_Sample.S_SampleID and displayValueUnit_PH.U_METHODSHORTNAME = workitem.U_METHODSHORTNAME

SUMMARY

column1: The Client's QC can't download the spec for this product.
CSM tried this link it went well,  but the client can't download this one. And the client feedback  their QC usually meet the similar problem for spec download.
Issue is created by (PR or Jira ticket link):
For some files that are big, the users need to wait several seconds before the files are downloaded into their device
* Once the user clicks on Download in hover action or action in 3 dots icon
we should display a loader to let the user know that file is downloading. Once downloaded is done, the message will disappear
(Enter any other details such as examples, links to requirements, etc. Any criteria that might help with fixing the problem. Attach screenshots if possible. More detail is better)
(If there is a way to work around the problem, place that information here)
* Link to Figma Dashboard /Figma Style Guide to respect guidelines
* API documentation filled in case of Public API (Swagger/Redoc)
I just tried on my send, I succeeded to download file
I’ll ask dev to check logs to see if we can know what is wrong for the end user

CHINES TIME 9:56 on {{2024-07-04}} ","08/Jul/24 3:18 PM;712020:d9c7e72a-15f6-40bf-a5d5-62dae24d573b;[~accountid:5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f] yes please, as I tried with no problem as well, but the customer user can’t ","08/Jul/24 3:21 PM;5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8;[~accountid:712020:d9c7e72a-15f6-40bf-a5d5-62dae24d573b], when asking for video recording, please advise to open the browser console tab so we can see if there is any error.

column2: http://fast.com] / etc )","08/Jul/24 3:44 PM;5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8;It’s an 18 MB file.  It would look like nothing is happening when the user clicks on the Download, but it might already be downloading.  But because the user internet is slow, the response is very late.

column1: [~accountid:5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f], for improvement we can change the DOWNLOAD button to a Downloading/ Loading button after clicking it, so the user will know it is already downloading.

column2: width=100%,alt=""image-20240708-074144.png""!","08/Jul/24 5:21 PM;5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8;[~accountid:712020:d9c7e72a-15f6-40bf-a5d5-62dae24d573b] , please advise the user to NOT click the Download button many times, because it will cancel previous downloads and starts a new one.  Click Download, wait for 1-3 minutes, and check the browser Downloads tab.","08/Jul/24 5:35 PM;5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8;This is how downloading BIG files on SLOW internet looks like. We need to show Downloading button/icon to block user from downloading repeatedly.

column1: The reason why no test information shown in the excel printout is because there is no Test in SBD page.  The ‘Specimen No’ and ‘Specimen Count’ need the ‘test or not test’ field to show or calculated the specimen count (e.g. not tested specimens will not be counted).
[~accountid:621f1e5e14cd24006907e4c5] Is it normal case without Tests informaitons in SBD ? If it’s normal, what’s the logic to show the ‘Specimen No’ and ‘Specimen Count’ ?

column1: It’s because ‘Test/Not Test’ field is empty, is it normal if the test/not test column is empty?

It is bug. In the original setup, when candidates click “Edit Test”, tests would be triggered with “tested” are shown in default (supposed they are all tested, and candidates will change to ‘not tested’ if needed).
It works in PP (example below) but not in PROD.
The reason why the 'tested' not shown as default is that there is no default value for u_specimenworkitem.u_tested in PROD.
It was fixed now, please check, thanks.","08/Jul/24 6:13 PM;621f1e5e14cd24006907e4c5;[~accountid:628a5f6cd5ec4f0069e6ce7e] Checked ok for point 1. Thanks.

Context
Some PEO reports may have several containers. These containers are filled into InspectorApp with their related info.
We ALREADY have the number of containers per report.
What is missing is the CONTAINER_INFO (HTS code, NOMS requirement...)
For that we need InspectorApp info (based on Operations feedback there is no other way to get it).
Currently, we cannot get this because we cannot associate the container info with the correct container.
We need a SUB_FIELD_ID column to associate the info to the correct sub field.
Basically on the left this is the order organization and on the right this is the current link status,

column1: The following is the SQL used to query the containers sub field. It is recommended that the search time range should not exceed one month, otherwise it will be slow.
left join AIDATAUSER.PARM_CLASSIFIED_KEYVALUE pck_st on pck_st.VALUE = ogi.SERVICE_TYPE and pck_st.CLASSIFICATION = 'SERVICE_TYPE'
left join AIDATAUSER.ORDER_PRODUCT op on op.ORDER_ID = ogi.ORDER_ID
left join AIDATAUSER.ORDER_PROD_CHECKLIST opc on opc.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID
left join AIDATAUSER.IP_GROUP ipg on ipg.GROUP_ID = opc.IP_TEMPLATE
left join AIDATAUSER.IP_GROUP_SECTION_FIELD ipgsf on ipgsf.GROUP_ID = ipg.GROUP_ID
left join AIDATAUSER.IP_SECTION ips on ips.ID = ipgsf.LINK_ID
left join AIDATAUSER.IP_SECTION_FIELD ipsf on ipsf.SECTION_ID = ips.ID
left join AIDATAUSER.IP_FIELDS ipf on ipf.FIELD_ID = ipsf.FIELD_ID
left join AIDATAUSER.ORDER_INSPECTION_RESULT oir on oir.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and oir.DELETE_TIME is null and oir.RESULT_TYPE like ips.ID
left join AIDATAUSER.PARM_CLASSIFIED_KEYVALUE pck_st on pck_st.VALUE = ogi.SERVICE_TYPE and pck_st.CLASSIFICATION = 'SERVICE_TYPE'
left join AIDATAUSER.ORDER_PRODUCT op on op.ORDER_ID = ogi.ORDER_ID
left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO container_id on container_id.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and container_id.LABEL = 'Container Identification Number'
left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO typeOfContainer on typeOfContainer.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and typeOfContainer.U_ID = container_id.U_ID and typeOfContainer.LABEL = 'Type of Container'
left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO totalQtyOfCtns on totalQtyOfCtns.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and totalQtyOfCtns.U_ID = container_id.U_ID and totalQtyOfCtns.LABEL = 'Total QTY of CTNs'
left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO sealNumber on sealNumber.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and sealNumber.U_ID = container_id.U_ID and sealNumber.LABEL = 'Seal Number'

left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO containerConditions on containerConditions.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and containerConditions.U_ID = container_id.U_ID and containerConditions.LABEL = 'Container Conditions'
left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO containerAge on containerAge.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and containerAge.U_ID = container_id.U_ID and containerAge.LABEL = 'Container Age'
left join CONTAINER_SUB_INFO loadingConditions on loadingConditions.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID and loadingConditions.U_ID = container_id.U_ID and loadingConditions.LABEL = 'Loading Conditions'

column1: *Commun part* for *CSM* or *PM* who creates a business enabler ticket
Aurelie Presset, a team user with a role of Administrator informed us that she wanted to delete the entity name “Franchise” as she made it by mistake.
This is for DIM administration role, deletion of entity that was were created by mistake.
The deleted option is not available in the network tab. Currently, we can only delete a site if we enter in the site profile and click in the options.
The deleted option should be available in the 3 dots icon of network table
Enter any background or reference that may help with developing the feature
Define here the KPI to measure the success of this ticket
* Link to Figma Dashboard /Figma Style Guide to respect guidelines
* API documentation filled in case of Public API (Swagger/Redoc)

KIK - Show a correct Error message when booking inspection of deleted purchaseOrderProductId,PL-22502,137250,Bug,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,High,,,,Zoe.zuo@qima.com,712020:d9c7e72a-15f6-40bf-a5d5-62dae24d573b,Zoe.zuo@qima.com,712020:d9c7e72a-15f6-40bf-a5d5-62dae24d573b,05/Jul/24 5:14 PM,26/Jul/24 3:23 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,client,qimaone,Support,,,When the client submit the inspection assignment, it pops up to ask cancel or not, which block the assignment.
# In the case of KIK, the PO was re-imported.
# Issue only happens when more than 1 product in booking.
# View the PO in 2 browser tabs.
# In tab 1, start booking inspection of the PO, add the 1 or 2 products, DO NOT submit yet.
# In tab 2, edit the PO, add again the same products, then remove the 1 or 2 products which has been added in the inspection by step 3, and Save the PO edition.
Reload the PO to get latest purchaseorderproductIds and start booking on the latest products.
When we have this booking conflict, and we the user clicks on Submit button, we should show an error message instead show CANCLE inspection modal:
Snarkbar error message: The product(s) you chose for this inspection have been removed from the PO(s). Please refresh the page and schedule again.

column1: [Cost saving] List of test checklists and inspections using in-app SCAN feature,PL-22497,137241,Business Enabler,Done,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,High,Done,Nan Chen,5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f,Nan Chen,5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f,Nan Chen,5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f,05/Jul/24 4:25 PM,10/Jul/24 11:28 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,10/Jul/24 11:28 PM,,,,,0,support,,,,,"h2. Context and reason why
With scandit, we pay 0.0875 euros per scan.
To save cost, Brand QIMA inspections want to remove in-app scan in QIMAone and ask the inspector to use a free app to do it.
* For all synced test checklists from QSP to QIMAone, it’s already the case.

Once the checklist is synced, there is no scan feature automatically enabled with synchronization, and no operation team member goes to edit the synced test checklist by adding scan as a mandatory requirement for the inspector, so the inspector scans with a free app, and customers are OK with it.
* However, QSP has some key account customers with special test checklists, which have been created in QIMAone (not synced from QSP), we may still this enabled scan feature.
So we need this list to check client by client if we can remove scan feature.
* List of test checklists having scan feature set as a mandatory requirement.
Property: Test checklist ID, Test checklist name, creation date
* List of inspections of last 3 months where the scan feature has been used = at least one test having Scan as a mandatory requirement.
Property: Inspection ID, workflow name, test checklist name + R-cloud number (if it’s possible)
Enter any background or reference that may help with developing the feature
Define here the KPI to measure the success of this ticket
* Link to Figma Dashboard /Figma Style Guide to respect guidelines
* API documentation filled in case of Public API (Swagger/Redoc)

column1: *Commun part* for *CSM* or *PM* who creates a business enabler ticket

This feature is for CONSUMER GOODS / PRODUCE, NOT for CONSUMER GOOD / PRODUCE
Put UI link here (*NOT* UX sandbox screens)
Modify this part if it doesn't fit your US
- If the value is too long, we display it with a maximum of 1 line, then display ""…"" with a tooltip
- If the value is one single long word, we need to cut it to fit into the component
- If there is no corresponding value, we display ""---""
In case of a new email, PM needs to add it to this confluence page and the template needs to be validated by the marketing team before development.
*Important remark: NOTIFUS will be out of service end of 2023, so please don't implement new email with NOTIFUS until we find a new external service*
PM needs to update the confluence page with new URL
PM needs to update the confluence page with new permission
If It's a *new permission for BRAND team user*, we MUST display this permission into QIMAone: settings/role/backoffice-user. Please respect permissions' order as in the confluence page.

column1: Regression Testing,AIC-8,137229,Task,In Progress,AIC,AI INSPECTOR CHATBOT,business,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,,,Highest,,Valentin Suppa-Gallezot,712020:bf81944f-da89-44a5-b50a-2d29cf99d704,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,Calvin Marshall,712020:2fb631a5-77a1-4cd0-a2bd-1c9dbbb28552,05/Jul/24 2:54 PM,22/Jul/24 5:20 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,24/Jul/24 12:00 AM,0,,,,,,"Temporary link until I can work out a more methodical system with Valentin and the inspection teams: [Inspector Chatbot testing.xlsx (sharepoint.com)
* Select key power users to conduct weekly regression testing and report findings

* Modify test reporting document so that we cand directly attribute a specific GI that users are testing against, this is so we can see if this is an issue with the model or if it is an issue with the GI
* If issue found with GI, [~accountid:63f742970154af3bb2b046de] [~accountid:712020:bf81944f-da89-44a5-b50a-2d29cf99d704] to define process to update the GI on adhoc basis
* After speaking with [~accountid:712020:f94edf25-0169-4381-9f2d-bb24ed1d4699] , we will need more specificity for the test grading i.e. ‘Needs Improvement’. There are two areas that we can focus on:
** Speed - please report the time taken to produce the full result, or if timeout issue, etc… (for this aspect, we can try different models)

** Accuracy - please help to relay the relative criticality of the issue observed (critical, major, minor) which could be translated to a % withing the existing grading system. (for this aspect, we can pull levers on the following)
*** Change the GI docs to include more mentions of customer, more precise information etc…

column1: Combined inspection: no button to combine sometimes
* It's normal. The custome needs to make sure that the first chosen product has a shipment date.
It's the combined inspection rule: we only show the add more button if the first product has a shipment date
However, they didn't understand why we needed them to help to record something. Jocelyn explained that for some errors, we cannot see them in our logs.
And we tried on our side to reproduce it, but we didn’t make it.
They also talked some features they wanted to have:
* Allow the inspector to create a test in the inspector app. CSM has created an insight for this one
* QIMAone doesn't judge pass and fail on the quantities part, if the expected quantities is not reaching.

We suggest them in this case, they just need to build a test such as: Is the produced quantity meeting the expectation? YES or NO. Moreover, as it's a test, so the inspector can put some pictures, comments if needed. They are OK with this and they will check what they should do with CSM.

So for this moment,I close this ticket. ","10/Jul/24 4:50 PM;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;[~accountid:712020:d9c7e72a-15f6-40bf-a5d5-62dae24d573b] Please log the time spent on this ticket!

column1: Remove stale ignored trivy issues 🧹,PL-22490,137197,Deployment subtask,Won't do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,Won't Do,,,Automation for Jira,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,Automation for Jira,557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077,04/Jul/24 11:23 PM,12/Jul/24 8:12 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,12/Jul/24 8:12 PM,,,,,0,support,,,,,"- Clone the latest version of the repository.
- Remove all CVEs from the .trivyignore file.

- Run the Trivy check locally by following the steps described in https://qima.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/IT/pages/1279394044/Runbook+-+Docker+image+vulnerabilities+scanning#Testing-the-new-image-locally . You can use the latest develop images to run the script https://github.com/asiainspection/k8s-apps-descriptors/blob/integration/kustomize/environments/apps-integration/kustomization.yml

- If the list of detected vulnerabilities differs from in any way, modify the .trivyignore file, commit the changes and create a Pull Request, eg. https://github.com/asiainspection/qima-platform/pull/7425

Based on the findings, create a task that’s linked to this ticket to fix the issue either on the current release or in the upcoming one.

At the beginning of the support sprint choose a person responsible for logs monitoring and assign them to this ticket. It is crucial to check logs on Thursday to see if the new prod release did not bring any new issues.
Apply these filters manually while investigating traces to extract useful information about slow requests: 👉 MinLatency:2000 /http/host:app.qimaone http.path:/api 👈

[IRP] Update definition of the autoalloc engine's scope,SP-17929,137180,Task,READY FOR DEV,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,N/A,,,,François NOYEZ,5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee,François NOYEZ,5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee,04/Jul/24 9:05 PM,08/Jul/24 4:43 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"In order to not have to update the autoallocation engine's code (which is duplicated at least 4 times in various other places, such as Dashboards) each time the autoallocation scope needs to be update, the Data Science team would like to update the engine one final time, in order to direct it to the QSP database in order to fetch all of the scope data (incuding the orders' service type and business unit scope data, as well as the inspectors' department scope data, instead of the just the orders' country scope data, like it does currently).
In order to do this, the Data Science teams needs to update the QSP data dedicated to represent the scope for those various types of data.
Basically, we need to run the following queries:
, TEXT = 'Operations - Inspector,Operations - ProQC Inspector,Operations - GOAL Inspector,Operations - ETIC Inspector,Operations - SBE Inspector'
Just added a comment in your DB PR [https://github.com/asiainspection/Oracle_Master/pull/2600
You can contact DBA jojo to run it in dev/pp/staging DB
* Does your change requrie QSP team to do any test? or you will test it by yourself in PP?
* What do you expect to deploy?
Got it. I have added a commit to the PR, in order to address your comment.
Ok for running the script in preprod first, I'll ask the DBA team.

* As far as I'm aware, only the autoallocation project is using those values for now, so I would say no. No, there is no autoallocation project in a preprod env, so I will ""test"" directly by running simulations with the prod env of the autoallocation. Anyway in that specific case it's fine, since the engine don't rely for now on those values for now, and the point of my current work is to start making it rely on them. But obviously I'll want to deploy this updated version of the engine only once the desired values in QSP are correct. So if there is ever a problem with those values, I can always rollback the autoallocation engine by myself, I won't need other people to rollback those values.

* I expect to deploy a new version of the engine which will start relying on those values that I want to update here in order to define the engine's scope, rather than having the engine's scope being hardcoded into the engine itself. The goal is to stop having to modify the engine's code each time the scope is modified, because updating the code is an expensive operations, since I have to modify the code of the engine itself AND modify every location where duplicated code exists (around 6 locations right now, mostly in sql procedures for dashboard computation). Instead, it's better if the scope can be parametrized like that.","05/Jul/24 4:50 PM;557058:297081ca-fbf0-42dd-a9a6-b6396a919ed6;Hi Francois,

Since no testing is needed from QSP team so please send your DB PR to DBA when needed and go ahead. I think you don’t have to follow QSP regular release window (Tuesday morning) and you can take care of this production chagne by yourself. Thanks","05/Jul/24 6:35 PM;5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee;Hi [~accountid:557058:297081ca-fbf0-42dd-a9a6-b6396a919ed6]

In that case, can I assume that, next time, for this specific kind of data update for the engine's scope, and as long as no particular action is required from one of QSP's teams, I can just create the PR in Oracle_Master, and directly check all that with the DBA team, with no need to involve the Apollo team?","08/Jul/24 3:23 PM;557058:297081ca-fbf0-42dd-a9a6-b6396a919ed6;Hi [~accountid:5c6179cd35db5c2e2e5ebaee] , I think yes if QSP dev or teating team no need to be involved in IRP auto allocation, you can do it and contact DBA team direclty, but please verify it carefully after change are made and rollback when it isn’t working as expected.
Please also cc Eric Wang and me in email when you contact DBA for data change in database for IRP auto allocation.
Alright, understood, I’ll edit the engine’s documentation in order to reflect that.",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,To Do,04/Jul/24 9:05 PM

Increase lambda logs retention to 30 days,PL-22477,137167,Task,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,,,,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,04/Jul/24 3:31 PM,04/Jul/24 4:14 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,,,,,,"Hi, currently logs retention is 1 week for QIMAone lambdas and we had a case to investigate between QSP and QIMAone sync but we were not able to retrieve the logs because the issues occurred a long time ago.
Increase lambda logs retention to 30 days for production environment and evaluate the cost first to challenge this proposal.
We could do this only for report forwarder/report generation and other critical lambdas to lower the cost if needed.
Context of the user story, why, what...
Enter any details, clarifications, answers to questions, or points about the implementation here
This feature is for CONSUMER GOODS / PRODUCE, NOT for CONSUMER GOOD / PRODUCE
Put UI link here (*NOT* UX sandbox screens)
Modify this part if it doesn't fit your US
- If the value is too long, we display it with a maximum of 1 line, then display ""…"" with a tooltip
- If the value is one single long word, we need to cut it to fit into the component
- If there is no corresponding value, we display ""---""
In case of a new email, PM needs to add it to this confluence page and the template needs to be validated by the marketing team before development.
*Important remark: NOTIFUS will be out of service end of 2023, so please don't implement new email with NOTIFUS until we find a new external service*
PM needs to update the confluence page with new URL
PM needs to update the confluence page with new permission
If It's a *new permission for BRAND team user*, we MUST display this permission into QIMAone: settings/role/backoffice-user. Please respect permissions' order as in the confluence page.

User Story
I want to add a new setting in QIMA customer
So that clients & suppliers will not see the number of workers info in booking details page
* Add a new setting in QIMA customer - *Audit Settings*
** Setting name: Hide number of workers info on booking details of client account
When “Yes”, need to select at least one service. For example, when MA is Yes in this setting,
* Hide the highlighted info in booking details page of ACA and mixed myQIMA,
* When editing order, hide the highlighted info
But it keeps the same on checkout page when creating the order
Given that a user in back-office
I can see a new setting in QIMA customer
When I changed the setting of master account
I can sync this setting to my subaccunts
When the setting for MA is Yes
Clients can see number of workers info in checkout page when placing the order

But can’t see number of workers info in booking details page and checkout page when editing the order",,Automation for Jira,Chengfu Xie,Mack QIMA - Integration with Djeco,PL-22474,137126,Business Enabler,To Do,PL,QIMAone,software,Cyril Lakech,5c34cd77ccec3834a866ea0d,,https://app.qimaone.com/,N/A,,,,Vincent Roche,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,Vincent Roche,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,03/Jul/24 10:09 PM,03/Jul/24 10:09 PM,26/Jul/24 11:04 PM,,,,,,0,QIMA_integrations,,,,,Integrate QIMAone with Microsoft Dynamics & Centrix for Djeco, France

Djeco, a customer based in France, is migrating to new ERP and PLM systems (Microsoft Dynamics & Centrix) in July 2024. They require an integration with QIMAone for lab testing, auto booking, and PDF exportation. This integration project will involve:
* Linking Microsoft Dynamics & Centrix systems with QIMAone.
#* Establish a connection between Microsoft Dynamics & Centrix and QIMAone.
#* Automate lab testing workflow from initial testing through to result recording.
#* Implement auto booking features that synchronize with QIMAone and the customer's new systems.
#* Enable seamless PDF exportation of relevant documents directly from QIMAone to the new ERP & PLM.
#* Ensure data transferred between systems is accurate and consistent.
#* Conduct comprehensive testing to confirm the functionality of lab testing, auto booking, and PDF exportation features.
# *Discovery*: Understand existing processes and workflows of Djeco and how they will transition to Microsoft Dynamics & Centrix.
# *Mapping*: Align QIMAone features with the new ERP & PLM requirements.
#* Create integration scripts and modules to establish connections.
#* Implement automation for lab testing and booking.
#* Validate the integration through rigorous testing.
# *Deployment*: Roll out the integration in the live environment.
# *Support*: Provide ongoing support post-deployment to ensure smooth operation and handle any issues that arise.

This integration aims to streamline Djeco’s processes, ensuring a smooth transition to their new systems while enhancing their operational efficiency.",,Vincent Roche,,,,,,,,,,,,,,61a778c4fe9f300068aeb9d8,,,,,,,,,,,,,,;03/Jul/24 10:09 PM;ug:003dfacd-f315-4b21-8971-d7860707f8ad;5400,,,,,,,,,,,0,5400,,,0,5400,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.approvals.internal.customfield.ApprovalsCFValue@6b00ab69,,,,,,,LIMSDEV,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,N/A,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,None,,,,,,,,,,,,,No,,,,{},,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"+*Current Behaviour:*+

PM needs to update the confluence page with new permission

column1: Looking at the code, AWS S3 content is validated for duplicates, not the database: [https://github.com/asiainspection/qima-platform/blob/develop/backend/api/src/main/java/com/qima/platform/service/inspection/InspectionImageService.java#L121-L124
If there are 2 repeated requests sent at a similar time, then it’s possible that the picture from the first request is not yet fully uploaded when the check is done.

We could reduce the probability of this situation occurring by adding a check also at the database level. Note: it would degrade the performance of uploading pictures from inspector app a bit and would cost 1-2 story points to develop.",02/Jul/24 9:18 PM;557058:f58131cb-b67d-43c7-b30d-6b58d40bd077;[~accountid:5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f] Please log the time spent on this ticket!,"02/Jul/24 9:19 PM;5ccad21acbc5a60fd804ce0f;[~accountid:61e654cfeb1fb600719af3f6] [~accountid:5cf71eaf47450a0ea7b4cef8] thanks for your analysis
As it’s first time we have this complains, I’ll close this ticket for now.

If it happens again, let’s deal with it. I want to make sure all the updates on the QIMA Customer can successfully log
So that the Tableau dashboards can correctly reflect the new change
When updating the customer profile at the QIMA Customer interface, will log the history but will not update the “update_time“ to the table *“CRM_COMPANY“*
Whenever the customer information changes, the correct update time should be logged on the related table.
* Interface change (Change the customer information manually)
* API change (Change the customer profile by calling our API)
